    <body>
        <sect1>
            <p>
                A <xml>note</xml> marks up a block of text which is
                important enough to need highlighting. Unlike the emphasis
                tags which tend to be used to mark up a single world,
                notes often mark a whole sentance, or a whole paragraph.
            </p>

            <sect2>
                <title>Example</title>

                <xmlroot name="sect1">
                    <element name="para">
                        This is quite a simple experiment,
                        <inline name="note" value="though you really should
                        wash your hands before you begin for best results"/>.
                        Other people have found it quite easy.
                    </element>
                </xmlroot>
            </sect2>
            
            <sect2>
                <title>Definition</title>
                
                <p>
                    A <xml>note</xml> may only contain basic text.
                </p>
            </sect2>
            
            <sect2>
                <title>Rendition</title>
                
                <p>
                    The text should be emphasised in some way, though not
                    overtly so. Simple italics will often be sufficient,
                    but a different background colour, or inline graphics,
                    may work.
                </p>
            </sect2>
        </sect1>
